<p>17 April 1918<br/>Wednesday<br/>It is still raining &amp; very cold. The news from the French Front continues to be bad. Baillene has been lost &amp; the situation in the North is grave.</p>
<p>1918 April 18<br/>Thursday<br/>Weather still cold and miserable. Things appear to be going not too well at the Front.</p>
<p>Nothing of interest to report in this Camp.</p>
